# Numen UI Lanes — rules for the lane/* worktrees

These rules govern the parallel UI worktrees that hang off `main`:
`lane/polish` (`~/virtuna-polish` — design tokens / system), `lane/frame`
(`~/virtuna-frame` — peripheral screens), `lane/shell` (`~/virtuna-shell` —
global chrome + states), and `lane/cursor-ui` (`~/virtuna-cursor` — Cursor
refinement). They run in PARALLEL with the **GSI milestone**
(`milestone/numen-gsi`, worktree `~/virtuna-numen-gsi`), which is horizontally
rebuilding the core verb surfaces (Profile / Simulate / Predict) while promising
the creator experience stays byte-identical. Stay in your lane to avoid
conflicts. Branch off `main`, not off another lane.

## 1. Design system — trust ONE source
- The **only** authoritative design references are `src/app/globals.css` (the `@theme` token
  block) and `docs/DESIGN-SYSTEM.md`. Read `docs/DESIGN-SYSTEM.md` before any visual work.
- **IGNORE these — they are STALE** (they describe the retired Raycast/coral/glass system):
  `CLAUDE.md` "Raycast Design Language Rules" section, `BRAND-BIBLE.md`, `docs/tokens.md`,
  `docs/components.md`, `docs/design-specs.json`, `docs/usage-guidelines.md`,
  `docs/motion-guidelines.md`, `docs/brand/`.
- Current system = **flat-warm charcoal + cream text + MONOCHROME-by-default (accent near-zero) + matte**:
  - bg `#262624` (`--color-background`), cream text `#ece7de` (`--cream-primary`) — **never `#fff`**
  - accent = **terracotta `#d97757`** (`--color-accent`), the brand mark (signal-red `#e23b2d` was trialed then reverted 2026-06-24 — the de-Claude lever is the near-zero DOSAGE, not the hue). Never legacy `#FF7F50`.
  - **ACCENT DOSAGE IS LOCKED — MONOCHROME BY DEFAULT, accent used REALLY sparingly, if at all.** A screen with ZERO accent is the norm, not a failure. Every accent use must be justified; aim for at most ONE accent element per view, often zero. The ONLY sanctioned uses: the single live presence/liveness dot, the lit constellation/SIM node, the brand mark. FORBIDDEN everywhere else — primary buttons, icon buttons, skill pills, chevrons, placeholders, tabs, toggles, links, borders, charts, badges, large fills, hover states, and anything "to make it pop." Read "Accent dosage (LOCKED)" in `docs/DESIGN-SYSTEM.md` before touching color.
  - **Primary actions are NEUTRAL cream** — use `--color-action` / `--color-action-foreground`, NOT the accent. (Composer send = cream button, dark glyph.)
  - accent-as-text on dark → `--color-accent-text`; soft tint bg → `--color-accent-soft`. Solid accent fill glyph → `--color-accent-foreground` (cream).
  - `--color-accent` (brand terracotta) ≠ `--color-error` (data/destructive red). Never conflate.
  - borders 6% (`rgba(255,255,255,0.06)`), hover 10%
  - **matte only**: no glass gradients, no glow, no white inset-shine. Flat + border + (rarely) `--shadow-float`.
  - Inter for all chrome; serif (`--font-serif`, Newsreader; Fraunces candidate) **only** for voice-moments (greeting/hero).
  - radius 4/6/8/12/16/20/24 — cards 12, inputs/buttons 8.
  - **Identity is carried by the constellation/SIM motif + serif voice + copy**, since color is now quiet. Invest there.
- **Always consume tokens, never hardcode hex.** No `#FF7F50`, `#07080a`, `#18191a`, `#fff`, no raw `#d97757`/`#e23b2d` in components (use `--color-accent`).
- Keep `src/components/reading/__tests__/reskin-matte.test.ts` GREEN (guards against coral/glass).

## 2. Lane ownership — DO NOT cross
- ✅ **`lane/polish` OWNS:** `src/app/globals.css` `@theme` tokens, `docs/DESIGN-SYSTEM.md`,
  `src/types/design-tokens.ts`, and the cross-cutting visual language. **ONLY this lane edits
  token *definitions*** — every other lane consumes them.
- ✅ **`lane/frame` OWNS:** peripheral screens GSI doesn't rebuild — landing/marketing, auth
  (login/signup/reset), settings, account, billing/pricing/paywall/trial routes.
- ✅ **`lane/shell` OWNS:** global chrome (nav/sidebar/header shell), error/404, non-home loading
  skeletons, motion/transitions.
- ✅ **`lane/cursor-ui`:** small visual refinement, scoped per task. Auto-wip OFF (see ui-workflow.mdc).
- ⛔ **Do NOT touch (the GSI milestone owns these):** `src/lib/**`, `src/app/api/**`, runners,
  engine, `supabase/**`, prompt/KC files, **and the verb-surface HOLD list in §3a**. If a UI
  change seems to need a backend change, STOP and flag it — don't edit backend here.
- All lanes **CONSUME** tokens (read `globals.css`); only `lane/polish` **DEFINES** them. A token
  rename or removal must originate in `lane/polish` and be coordinated.

## 3. Coupled surfaces — visual via the token seam, don't fork-edit
The core verb surfaces are being actively rebuilt by the GSI milestone (their data shape / props /
block schemas are in flux). Polish them through the **TOKEN SEAM** — change a token in `lane/polish`
and they inherit the new look without anyone editing their component files. Do **NOT** fork a
parallel edit of these components, and do NOT change the props/data contracts or block schemas.

### 3a. ⛔ GSI HOLD list — do NOT edit (guaranteed merge conflict)
`milestone/numen-gsi` (worktree `~/virtuna-numen-gsi`) is horizontally rewriting these surfaces.
Leave them untouched until the matching GSI phase lands on `main`:
- **Home empty state + starter chips** — `src/components/app/home/**`
- **Composer / inbox** — `src/components/app/home/composer.tsx` + `composer-controls.tsx`
- **Audience picker / library** — `src/components/audience/**`, routes `src/app/(app)/audience/*`
- **AudienceLens / ambient reactor / presence** — `src/components/audience-lens/**`
- **Thread / skill cards / reaction cards** — `src/components/thread/**`
- **Skill menu · trust badges (Validated/Directional) · the Read output view**

Want a component-level tweak on one of these? Either (a) **wait** until GSI lands that phase to
`main`, then polish on top, or (b) **hand the tweak into the GSI session** (it's already editing
those files). Never fork a parallel edit — that's the merge war.

## 4. Conflict hygiene
- Rebase onto `origin/main` frequently (`git fetch origin && git rebase origin/main`) — and again
  before opening a PR, to catch GSI's merges as each phase lands.
- Keep PRs small and per-surface; merge often to minimize drift. The GSI milestone merges `main`
  into its branch at each phase boundary, so it picks up your token/frame changes incrementally.
- Commit format `type(surface): description`. Atomic commits.

## 5. Verify before done
- `npm run lint` + typecheck clean.
- Visual check in the browser (or screenshot) for any surface you change.
- Don't say "should work" — show it.
